column16: Anhui Government recommended to during the festival period, the general public is requested not to organize or participate in non-essential gathering activities, reduce the flow of people, advocate the citizens to "delay red matters as much as possible, handle white matters briefly, and do not hold banquets", and advocate family dinner gatherings with no more than 10 people. column28: According to Beijing CDC, from 0:00 on January 22, 2022 to the end of March, those who enter and return to Beijing need to carry out a nucleic acid test within 72 hours after arriving in Beijing (commuters continue to follow the existing policies and regulations). column35: The Chongqing government provided a new relief package to help those who work in the service industry. The relief package includes tax relief, rent relief and subsidies for expenditures of preventing Covid-19.   Workers in the productive and life service industry are provided 10% and 15% tax deduction. Small enterprises and individual proprietorship who rent government-owned houses are provided 3 months rent reduction. Subsidies for Covid-19 preventing costs are no less than 50% of the total expenditure. column10: Although Wuchuan county only controls the central urban area, it actually requires the suspension of schools in the whole county.  see the link:  http://web.archive.org/web/20220323130402/https://www.guizhou.gov.cn/zwgk/yqfkzccs/dsjzccs/202203/t20220315_72996161.html
column13: All public entertainment and leisure places in Wuchuan County were closed. Closed public entertainment and leisure places such as cinemas, chess and card rooms, mahjong halls, KTVs, Internet cafes, bars, bathing and foot therapy centers in the county continued to be closed.  see the link:http://web.archive.org/web/20220323130402/https://www.guizhou.gov.cn/zwgk/yqfkzccs/dsjzccs/202203/t20220315_72996161.html
column16: Wuchuan County stopped all large-scale activities. "Red and white festivities" and banquets and gatherings in the county will be suspended, and all personnel are not allowed to participate in crowded gatherings, folk customs and religious activities. Funeral venues will continue to suspend funeral activities and only accept cremation and ashes.  see the link:http://web.archive.org/web/20220323130402/https://www.guizhou.gov.cn/zwgk/yqfkzccs/dsjzccs/202203/t20220315_72996161.html
column19: Wuchuan County stopped all large-scale activities. column22: Although Wuchuan county only controls the central urban area, it actually requires the suspension of bus and taxi operations in the whole county.  see the link:http://web.archive.org/web/20220323130402/https://www.guizhou.gov.cn/zwgk/yqfkzccs/dsjzccs/202203/t20220315_72996161.html
column25: Wuchuan County suspended all unnecessary flows. All communities and communities implement closed management, all personnel are strictly isolated at home, and personnel flow is strictly prohibited. Strictly implement "home isolation and staying at home", and the community will uniformly organize the procurement of living materials and deliver them to the door. For those who need to go out under special circumstances such as emergency medical treatment, the community shall arrange special personnel for special vehicles, do a good job in personal protection throughout the whole process, and transfer them in a closed loop for medical treatment.  see the link:http://web.archive.org/web/20220323130402/https://www.guizhou.gov.cn/zwgk/yqfkzccs/dsjzccs/202203/t20220315_72996161.html

column10: In Wuchuan County,Primary and secondary schools continue to implement online teaching, and boarding schools continue to implement closed management.see the link:http://web.archive.org/web/20220329102025/https://m.thepaper.cn/baijiahao_17242302
column13: In Wuchuan County, closed public entertainment and leisure places such as cinemas, chess and card rooms, mahjong halls, KTVs, Internet cafes, bars, bathing and pedicure centers continue to suspend business.  see the link:http://web.archive.org/web/20220329102025/https://m.thepaper.cn/baijiahao_17242302
column16: In Wuchuan County, large-scale gatherings such as large-scale meetings, banquet gatherings, folk activities, weddings and weddings, and market town fairs will continue to be suspended.see the link:http://web.archive.org/web/20220329102025/https://m.thepaper.cn/baijiahao_17242302
column19: In Wuchuan County, large-scale gatherings such as large-scale meetings, banquet gatherings, folk activities, weddings and weddings, and market town fairs will continue to be suspended.see the link:http://web.archive.org/web/20220329102025/https://m.thepaper.cn/baijiahao_17242302
column22: Wuchuan County will continue to strengthen the control of public transport. Online car-hailing, passenger cars, and buses continue to be suspended. Private cars and official vehicles flow in an orderly manner in the area under strict implementation of preventive measures such as disinfection and sterilization, and drivers and passengers wearing masks; cruise taxis resume operations under strict implementation of preventive measures such as disinfection and sterilization, and drivers and passengers wearing masks.see the link:http://web.archive.org/web/20220329102025/https://m.thepaper.cn/baijiahao_17242302

column16: In Yuzhou, Henan, fairs and temple fairs need not be held, celebrating events need be postponed, and funerals need be held briefly.  See: http://archive.today/oQg7F

column25: On January 31, 2022, Yuzhou is fully unblocked. Apart from the situation that those who have not been released from home isolation in the city had to strictly follow home isolation measures, people are not required to stay at home.   See: http://archive.today/oQg7F
column28: On January 31, 2022, Yuzhou is fully unblocked. The entire city has lifted the management of the closed control area, the management control area, and the prevention area, and transferred to normalized epidemic prevention and control.  See: https://archive.ph/oQg7F

column13: From February 7, 2022, Yuzhou tourist attractions, outdoor stadiums, parks and other outdoor venues will be reopened in an orderly manner; Internet cafes, cinemas, KTV, amusement halls and other cultural and entertainment venues and religious venues, libraries, gymnasiums, science and technology museums, training institutions, bathing centers and other indoor crowded places continue to be closed. column22: From February 7, 2022, on the premise of strictly implementing various normalized epidemic prevention and control measures, public transportation in Yuzhou will resume normal traffic in an orderly manner.    See: http://archive.today/77Vtt

column28: On March 13, our province has announced the health management measures of "14 days of centralized isolation for medical observation" for all people coming to (returning) to Hubei in Shanghai. However, in recent days, some people still come to (return) to Hubei by public transportation or self-driving every day. We especially remind those who intend to come (return) from Shanghai to learn about the isolation policy of our province in advance; do a good job of personal protection on the way to (returning) to Hubei; and after returning to Hubei, they should take the initiative to declare to the community and cooperate with the 14-day centralized isolation.

column10: Elementary Schools and Middle Schools in Hainan Province have announced that all students and school faculties returning school on Feburary 17 for the new semester must show their health code and travel code. column10: The Harbin Education Bureau announced that since March 14 2022, some primary and secondary schools in Harbin will switch from offline teaching to online teaching. The details are as follows. Daowai District continues to implement online teaching; Daoli District, Nangang District, Xiangfang District, Pingfang District, Songbei District, Shuangcheng District, and Wuchang City primary and secondary schools (including secondary vocational schools) will switch from offline teaching to online teaching; the remaining ten districts and counties (cities) will be assessed by the local epidemic situation headquarters and decide whether to switch between online and offline teaching in primary and secondary schools within the jurisdiction. All kindergartens in the city will be closed, and all kinds of off-campus education and training institutions will stop teaching offline. In addition, all colleges and universities within the administrative area of Harbin will implement closed management; students do not leave school or leave Harbin. The resumption of offline teaching will be announced later.    In addition, on March 15, the Heilongjiang Provincial Civil Service Bureau and the Heilongjiang Provincial Personnel Examination Center issued an announcement, deciding to postpone the 2022 written examination for civil servants in Heilongjiang Province, which was originally scheduled to be held on March 26 and 27. The restart time of the written test and related arrangements will be notified separately according to the epidemic prevention and control situation.    See The Paper news website.    Archived: https://web.archive.org/web/20220316222216/https://m.thepaper.cn/baijiahao_17109607  https://web.archive.org/web/20220316222231/https://t.ynet.cn/baijia/32400264.html
column13: From the Announcement No. 53 of Harbin's COVID-19 Work Headquarter, since March 14 2022, the following policies will be implemented.    First, chess and card room (mahjong hall), bath, cinema, theater, karaoke hall, dance hall, bar, pedicure shop, massage parlor, game hall, Internet cafe, script killing, board game bar, library, escape room, indoor sports and fitness place, indoor children amusement projects, small hotels located in basements or semi-basements, various offline education and training institutions and other places with relatively closed spaces will be temporarily closed. Religious sites will be temporarily closed.     Secondly, Individual clinics will be closed. Welfare institutions, old-age service institutions, and mental health institutions implement will be under fully closed management, and personnel will be prohibited from entering and leaving. Aged care institutions will suspend the admission of newly admitted elderly people and stop visiting activities. The public security, judicial and administrative prisons will be under closed management, and family members who have direct contact will be suspended from visiting.    Thirdly, all construction sites under construction will be under closed management, and the employees of enterprises and institutions will not be allowed to leave the resident and operating sites unless necessary, and will strictly implement the "two points and one line" commuting mode.    Fourthly, various administrative enterprises and institutions at all levels will start to implement flexible working system, staggered commute to and from get off work, and actively advocate online office and home office as well. Comprehensively implement measures such as nucleic acid testing and screening, daily ventilation and disinfection, and daily health monitoring of employees.     Fifthly, all social catering service units (including food sales units that provide dine-in) will suspend dine-in, but can provide in-store pick-up and take-out ordering services; encourage the implementation of "contactless" delivery.    See The Paper news website.    Archived: https://web.archive.org/web/20220316162526/https://m.thepaper.cn/baijiahao_17127569
column16: From the Announcement No. 53 of Harbin's COVID-19 Work Headquarter, since March 14 2022, religious sites will be temporarily closed and collective religious activities will be suspended. All performances will be suspended. All kinds of night market operations will be suspended.    In addition, large-scale conferences, activities, forums, trainings, performances, exhibitions and sales promotions, etc. will be suspended. Public activities such as garden tours, temple fairs, folk customs, and square dances will be suspended. Also, the banquets or marriage affairs should be delayed; funeral affairs should be kept simple.    See The Paper news website.    Archived: https://web.archive.org/web/20220316162526/https://m.thepaper.cn/baijiahao_17127569
column19: From the Announcement No. 53 of Harbin's COVID-19 Work Headquarter, since March 14 2022, scenic spots must strictly implement the requirements of quotas, reservations, and staggered peaks, implementing time-sharing reservations, scan codes (health codes, itinerary codes) to enter the park. The number of tourists that can be admitted instantly shall not exceed 50% of the maximum capacity; the internal performances of scenic spots and scenic spots shall be suspended.     In addition, it is forbidden to gather together in various forms such as chatting, playing cards, and gatherings indoors, such as small shops in rural areas, and advocate villagers to visit and walk less as much as possible. column28: From the Announcement No. 53 of Harbin's COVID-19 Work Headquarter, since March 14 2022, the scenic spots in Harbin do not accept tourism groups and tourists outside Harbin. It is forbidden to organize cross-border tourism (outside the Heilongjiang province). It is strictly forbidden to receive tourism groups from epidemic-related areas, and it is strictly prohibited to organize groups to travel to epidemic-related areas.    In addition, those who return to Harbin from port cities in the province and outside the province must hold a negative nucleic acid test certificate within 48 hours. After arrival, they should conduct a free landing test. If people cannot do this right away, they should completed within 12 hours after arriving at their destination. Free landing test and report to the community (village) where people live.    See The Paper news website. column35: On March 16 2022, the Harbin Municipal People's Government issues the "Implementation Measures for Several Financial Policies of Harbin City on Further Supporting Small, Medium and Micro-sized Enterprises and Individual Industrial and Commercial Households to Stable Production and Operation in Response to the Impact of the Epidemic", which mainly to clarify how the 2 billion funds for stabilizing and stabilizing jobs should be used. The policy mainly includes three aspects. First, implement the financial support policy for stabilizing enterprises and jobs, and encourage banks to grant loans to qualified small, medium and micro enterprises and individual industrial and commercial households through the implementation of a risk sharing mechanism for government bank guarantee institutions. The second part is to provide loan discounts to eligible enterprises. The third part is that the financing guarantee company funded by the municipal finance will reduce or exempt the guarantee fee for eligible enterprises. The scope of the financial support policy to stabilize stability and stability of jobs includes: small, medium, and micro enterprises (including individual industrial and commercial households) that have encountered difficulties in five industries, including wholesale and retail, accommodation and catering, cultural tourism, transportation and logistics, and manufacturing, which have been greatly affected by the epidemic. The loan discount policy supports: small, medium and micro enterprises and individual industrial and commercial households engaged in wholesale and retail, accommodation and catering, education, tourism, culture, sports and entertainment, transportation and other six industries in Harbin City.    See Heilongjiang Daily website.    Archived: https://web.archive.org/web/20220316232052/https://cj.sina.com.cn/articles/view/1898885525/712eb195001011arp

column13: From the Announcement No. 55 of Harbin's COVID-19 Work Headquarter, since March 19 2022, the following policy will be implemented.     1. In addition to farmers' markets, shopping malls, supermarkets, morning markets, pharmacies, gas stations, catering enterprises (only providing self-pickup, take-out ordering services) and other basic livelihood security business places, other business places and stores should all be closed.    2. Places that are allowed to operate must strictly implement various prevention and control measures, such as "scanning code, temperature measurement, wearing masks", staggered peak current limit, daily disinfection, employee health monitoring, and employees should hold a negative nucleic acid test certificate within 48 hours to go to work. Those who do not comply with the epidemic prevention and control regulations will be ordered to suspend business for rectification, and can resume operations only after passing the examination.    3. During the nucleic acid of all citizens in Harbin, all people entering the shopping malls, supermarkets, pharmacies, farmers markets, morning markets and other business places must hold a negative nucleic acid test certificate within 48 hours. Those who do not have a certificate are prohibited from entering. Localities can take necessary management measures according to the actual situation.     4. Express delivery and meals takeout companies should strengthen the health management of employees. All employees should undergo nucleic acid testing once a day. In principle, express delivery and meals takeaway companies' employees are not allowed to enter the residential area, and contactless delivery methods shall be implemented. Those who need to enter the communities should use smart express cabinets, post stations, etc. to deliver express deliveries must strictly implement measures such as "scanning code, temperature measurement, wearing masks", piece-by-piece disinfection, and strictly inspect delivery personnel for 24 hours Negative certificate of nucleic acid test.    5. During the nucleic acid testing of all citizens, all levels of government agencies, enterprises and institutions in Harbin shall strictly manage all entry and exit channels, strictly implement measures such as "scanning codes, measuring temperature, and wearing masks" for all entry personnel, and conduct inspections for 48 hours negative certificate of COVID-19 nucleic acid testing.    6. The business of various types of administrative examination and approval service halls, petition reception places and other window units in our city can be handled online or by self-service, all of which are handled in a "non-face-to-face" manner. And implement various epidemic prevention and control measures.    7. All kinds of enterprises should take the main responsibility for epidemic prevention and control, and strictly implement the "two points and one line" commuting mode.    See The Paper news website.    Archived: https://web.archive.org/web/20220323133745/https://m.thepaper.cn/baijiahao_17203544

column25: From the Announcement No. 55 of Harbin's COVID-19 Work Headquarter, since March 19 2022, the closed control area implements regional closure, staying at home, not entering, and door-to-door service; the control area advocates that personnel do not go out, and if it is necessary to go out, strictly implement people not to leave the area, pick up items at different peaks, and strictly prohibit gatherings.    Outside the control area shall be managed according to the prevention area, and entrances and exits can be reduced according to the actual situation, and the measures of "scan code, temperature measurement, and wearing a mask" shall be strictly implemented. Non-residents of the community (village), vehicles (Except emergency protection, medical rescue, garbage cleaning, etc.) is forbidden to enter. Outsiders who really need to enter the community (village) must hold a negative nucleic acid test certificate within 48 hours and be strictly registered and approved before entering.    All home isolation medical observation personnel must comply with relevant regulations, and strictly implement the management measures of sticking seals, staying at home, and providing door-to-door services.    All home health monitoring and isolating personnel must strictly implement the management measures of not going out unless necessary, not participating in various collective activities, not having meals, and not gathering.    Anyone who violates the regulations of home isolation medical observation and home health monitoring will be transferred to centralized isolation, the control time will be recalculated, and the expenses will be borne by themselves.    See The Paper news website.    Archived: https://web.archive.org/web/20220323133745/https://m.thepaper.cn/baijiahao_17203544
column28: From the Announcement No. 55 of Harbin's COVID-19 Work Headquarter, since March 19 2022, the following policy will be implemented.     1. People Daoli, Daowai, Nangang, Xiangfang, Pingfang, Songbei, and Hulan districts in Harbin are strictly restricted from leaving the main urban area. Those who really need to leave the main urban area to enter other districts and cities must hold negative nucleic acid test report within 48 hours and the "Longjiang Health Code" green code.    2. People from Acheng, Shuangcheng District and Bayan, Mulan, Tonghe, Yilan, Fangzheng, Yanshou, and Binxian 7 counties cannot leave the districts and counties unless necessary. Entering other districts and counties in Harbin must hold a negative nucleic acid test certificate within 48 hours the "Longjiang Health Code" green code.    3. Personnel and vehicles related to emergency, epidemic prevention, commuting, important official duties, and people's livelihood security are not subject to entry and exit restrictions, but must hold a negative nucleic acid test certificate within 48 hours. People and vehicles that really need to go out for medical treatment are not subject to access restrictions.    4. The general public is requested to stay in Harbin unless necessary. Those who do need to leave Harbin must hold a negative nucleic acid test certificate within 48 hours, and travel with the "Longjiang Health Code" green code.    See The Paper news website.    Archived: https://web.archive.org/web/20220323133745/https://m.thepaper.cn/baijiahao_17203544

column13: From the Announcement No. 56 of Harbin's COVID-19 Work Headquarter, since March 27 2022, besides continue implementing the policies in the No.53 and No.55 Announcements, Harbin's daily consumer goods wholesale and retail markets (excluding farmers' wholesale markets), commercial complexes, and department stores (excluding supermarkets) will be temporarily closed.    Next, municipal, district/county (city)'s institutions, except for the staff who undertake the tasks of epidemic prevention and control and people's livelihood security, all other people should work from home. All types of enterprises should strictly implement the main responsibility for epidemic prevention and control.    In addition, suspend non-productive offline business activities such as consulting services, insurance agents, and legal services. Enterprises with normal production and operation (including agricultural production) should consolidate their main responsibilities, encrypt the frequency of nucleic acid sampling of employees (farmers), strengthen the health monitoring of employees (farmers), and strictly implement "code scanning, temperature measurement, wearing masks" and other items Epidemic prevention measures. Qualified enterprises can implement closed management.    Furthermore, the window of public utilities such as water, electricity, gas and communication implements "no face-to-face" online processing and online payment. During the epidemic prevention and control period, non-malicious arrears will not be charged with water, electricity, gas, network, or shutdown, and no late fee will be charged when making up.    See The Paper news website.    Archived: https://web.archive.org/web/20220327221821/https://m.thepaper.cn/baijiahao_17332503

column25: From the Announcement No. 56 of Harbin's COVID-19 Work Headquarter, since March 27 2022, the following policy will be implemented.     1. In principle, only one entrance and exit is reserved for each community, and zoning management measures can be adopted for super-large communities.    2. During the nucleic acid testing period for all employees in the area, residents are in principle at home, and each household can arrange 1 person every two days to purchase daily necessities nearby under the premise of strict personal protection, and each time out shall not exceed 2 hours. Entry and exit personnel strictly check the negative nucleic acid test certificate within 48 hours. People and vehicles that really need to go out for medical treatment are not subject to access restrictions.    3. Personnel entering and leaving must strictly implement the measures of "scanning codes, measuring temperature, and wearing masks".    4. For staff who really need to go out to work, the affiliated unit must consolidate the main responsibility, manage it strictly, and strictly monitor the health of the employees. Enter and leave the community (village) with the work certificate issued by the unit, and go to and from work "two points and one line".    5. Persons and vehicles outside the community (village) are prohibited from entering. Those who really need to enter must strictly follow the community (village) registration and approval procedures; personnel and vehicles such as emergency rescue, fire rescue, medical rescue, garbage removal, etc. except.    6. Courier service and takeaway industry personals are not allowed to enter the community (village), and contactless delivery will be implemented.    See The Paper news website.    Archived: https://web.archive.org/web/20220327221821/https://m.thepaper.cn/baijiahao_17332503

column44: From the Announcement No. 56 of Harbin's COVID-19 Work Headquarter, since March 27 2022, the following policy will be implemented.     1. All personnel in the administrative area of Harbin shall complete the nucleic acid test of all personnel in each round of the area in accordance with the requirements of "all citizens must be inspected and no one will be left behind".    2. Citizens are requested to pay close attention to the nucleic acid testing time of all staff in the area, participate in the nucleic acid testing at different times according to the notification of the community (village) where they are located, and take personal protection. After the test, return to the residence immediately.    3. During the nucleic acid sampling period, be sure to obey the on-site command, abide by the on-site order, and implement prevention and control measures such as wearing masks, queuing, and maintaining distance.    4. Fully carry out the "knock on the door" operation. Public security officers, grassroots community (village) personnel and volunteers will form a working group to jointly carry out the "knock on the door" operation, registering residents one by one to ensure that no one is missed.    5. Those who do not participate in the nucleic acid testing of all employees in the region will be assigned a yellow code to their "Longjiang Health Code" and will be notified via SMS. For those who have not participated in more than two rounds, the community (village) will take strict control measures.    See The Paper news website.    Archived: https://web.archive.org/web/20220327221821/https://m.thepaper.cn/baijiahao_17332503

Deliberately destroying medical and epidemic prevention property and facilities;  7. Use the epidemic to drive up prices;  8. Other behaviors that interfere with the prevention and control of the epidemic.    See The Paper news website. column13: From the Announcement No. 57 of Harbin's COVID-19 Work Headquarter, since April 1 2022, the following policies will be implemented.    1. The agricultural business activities will be orderly resumed. The agricultural businesses, distribution and maintenance of agricultural machineries, accessories and other business places and stores in the Harbin city will resume operation in an orderly manner. Various prevention and control measures such as peak staggering and current limiting, daily disinfection and employee health monitoring shall be strictly implemented. In addition, strictly implement the prevention and control measures such as "code scanning (health code + travel code), temperature measurement, wearing masks" and checking the negative certificate of nucleic acid test within 48 hours.    2. Carry out agricultural agency services in an orderly manner. For the residents in the sealed and controlled areas and the farmers who are carrying out medical observation and health monitoring, all townships and villages shall uniformly organize the purchase, collection, storage, custody and farming services of agricultural materials.    3. The auto repair operations will be resumed. The auto repair stores that meet the epidemic prevention and control standards in the Harbin city will resume operation in an orderly manner, and an appointment system will be implemented. Also, strictly implement various prevention and control measures such as peak staggering and current limiting, daily disinfection and employee health monitoring. In addition, strictly implement "code scanning (health code + travel code), temperature measurement and wearing masks" for all entrants, and check the negative certificate of nucleic acid test within 48 hours. The number of instantaneous customers shall not exceed the total number of maintenance stations.    See The Paper news website.    Archived: http://web.archive.org/web/20220407095623/https://m.thepaper.cn/baijiahao_17432242
column28: From the Announcement No. 57 of Harbin's COVID-19 Work Headquarter, since April 1 2022, the following policies will be implemented.    1. The Harbin city will liberalize travel restrictions on agricultural production in an orderly manner. All kinds of new agricultural entities and farmers in epidemic free villages and towns implement the "two points and one line" operation mode, and there are no restrictions on their operation and travel within their jurisdiction. For cross Township operations, report to the village where the operation is located in advance, and disinfect the agricultural machinery when entering and leaving. Personnel shall hold the negative certificate of nucleic acid test within 48 hours, and shall not take public transport for "point-to-point" operation. Farmers living in cities and towns must return home in an orderly manner with a negative nucleic acid test certificate within 48 hours to carry out agricultural activities, and those who are undergoing medical observation and health monitoring will be postponed to return home. Personnel from epidemic areas outside the administrative area of Harbin are prohibited from coming to Kazakhstan to carry out agricultural production and work activities.    2. The orderly and smooth the green channel of agricultural materials transportation will be implemented. Cross regional "point-to-point" transportation is allowed for vehicles transporting agricultural means of production and agricultural machines and tools. The drivers and passengers shall be managed in a closed manner throughout the whole process, and unloading and handover shall be conducted without contact. Among them, the transport vehicles from the districts in the Harbin city can be delivered to the designated place of the village for contactless delivery. For transport vehicles from outside the districts in the Harbin city, the receiving unit shall report to the district’s headquarters in advance. Also, implement "landing detection" for drivers and passengers (if the "landing detection" has been carried out at the entry checkpoint, the detection will not be repeated). The vehicles shall be disinfected and escorted by special personnel to the designated place for contactless delivery. During the period, standardized personal protection shall be done.    See The Paper news website.    Archived: http://web.archive.org/web/20220407095623/https://m.thepaper.cn/baijiahao_17432242

column10: From the Announcement No.14 of Hegang City's COVID-19 Work Headquarter, since April 4 2022, the following policies will be implemented.    Primary and secondary schools and kindergartens in the city will be opened in an orderly manner after passing the inspection and evaluation by the education department. Strictly implement "one school, one policy". Closed management should be implemented on campus, and the "two points and one line" commuting mode of teachers, students and teaching staff should be implemented. Strictly implement 20% nucleic acid sampling every day, and do a good job in daily health monitoring and campus killing. At the same time, do a good job in the health monitoring and management of students' parents.    See Guangming Net website.    Archived:  http://web.archive.org/web/20220408213823/https://m.gmw.cn/baijia/2022-04/04/1302881964.html
column13: From the Announcement No.14 of Hegang City's COVID-19 Work Headquarter, since April 4 2022, the following policies will be implemented.    1. All kinds of farmers' markets, morning markets, shopping malls, supermarkets, grocery stores, fruit and vegetable stores and other places in the city can be opened in an orderly manner after passing the inspection and evaluation by the territorial and competent industrial departments. And strengthen management. All places should strictly implement code scanning, wearing masks and other prevention and control measures, and obey the management and guidance of managers. The masses shall leave in time after purchasing, and shall not gather to stay.    2. Medical institutions at all levels shall implement closed management and prohibit visits. The private clinic was closed. The drugstore resumed business. The "four types" of drugs such as fever and cough strictly implemented the "filling and reporting", timely pushed the information to the local community for follow-up, and implemented closed-loop management.    3. Express delivery, takeout and other enterprises should further strengthen the implementation of main responsibilities and strengthen the health management of employees. All personnel shall conduct nucleic acid test once a day.    4. Catering service units shall be opened in an orderly manner after passing the inspection and evaluation by the local competent department. We should strictly implement the main responsibility for epidemic prevention and control, do a good job in health monitoring of employees, and ensure food and personnel safety. Advocate the provision of self-service and takeout delivery services. Indoor dining shall be limited by 50% of the approved number of people, with less than 6 people per table and dining at separate tables in the hall.    5. Barber shops can be opened orderly after passing the inspection and evaluation by the local competent department. 50% flow restriction and reservation system shall be implemented, and there shall be no customers waiting in the store. Staff and customers should wear masks throughout the process. Strictly implement code scanning, temperature measurement, ventilation, killing and other prevention and control measures to achieve "one customer, one use and one disinfection".    6. The construction site under construction shall be subject to closed management. Employees of enterprises and institutions who live in centralized accommodation shall not leave the site and operation place unless necessary, and the "two points and one line" commuting mode shall be strictly implemented. Strengthen personnel health monitoring and nucleic acid detection.    7. Party and government organs, enterprises and institutions in the city resumed normal office order. The affiliated units shall compact the main responsibility and implement epidemic prevention measures such as ventilation and killing. Supervise and urge the cadres and workers of the unit to strictly abide by the provisions on epidemic prevention and implement the requirements of "five leading" and "three trying". Strengthen personal protection and advocate the "two points and one line" commuting mode.    8. Chess and card room (mahjong Hall), bathing, cinema, concert hall, dance hall, billiards hall, bar, foot therapy shop, massage parlor, game hall, Internet cafe, script killing, board game bar, library, secret room escape, small theater, health salon, tea house, coffee shop, milk tea shop, ball hall, gym, swimming pool and other indoor leisure, fitness and entertainment places, indoor children's amusement projects, beauty salons, various offline education and training institutions Health products conference marketing training points, health lecture publicity points, various health care equipment experience stores and other places with relatively closed space will be suspended, and the opening hours will be notified separately.    See Guangming Net website.    Archived:  http://web.archive.org/web/20220408213823/https://m.gmw.cn/baijia/2022-04/04/1302881964.html
column16: From the Announcement No.14 of Hegang City's COVID-19 Work Headquarter, since April 4 2022, the following policies will be implemented.    1. Epidemic prevention measures shall be strictly implemented in scenic spots. The system of time sharing, peak staggering, reservation and current limit shall be implemented according to the maximum carrying capacity. Should do well in environmental sanitation and disinfection of public areas.    2. Strictly implement the epidemic prevention and control measures during the Qingming Festival. All funeral service units suspended on-site sacrifice activities and guided the masses to cherish the memory of their ancestors in simple ways such as online sacrifice.    3. All kinds of religious places will be closed to the outside world and collective religious activities will be suspended. Welfare institutions, elderly care institutions, mental health institutions and detention centers in the city continue to implement fully closed management, and personnel are prohibited from entering and leaving.    4. Suspend holding large-scale conferences, activities, forums, training, performances, exhibitions and sales promotions, and suspend mass activities such as garden tours, folk customs and square dances. It is advocated that red affairs should not be handled, white affairs should be handled simply, and other banquets should not be handled.    5. During the Qingming and May Day holidays, the general public should adhere to the local holiday, avoid or reduce going out, and do not participate in gathering activities. When you really need to go out, you must wear a mask correctly, do a good job in personal health monitoring, and jointly consolidate and expand the hard won prevention and control achievements. Those who fail to implement the epidemic prevention and control measures as required, resulting in the risk of epidemic spread, will be investigated for responsibility according to law.    See Guangming Net website.    Archived:  http://web.archive.org/web/20220408213823/https://m.gmw.cn/baijia/2022-04/04/1302881964.html

column22: From the Announcement No.14 of Hegang City's COVID-19 Work Headquarter, since April 4 2022, the following policies will be implemented.    Lift traffic control. Buses and taxis in the city doing a good job in personal protection of drivers, after taking measures such as killing and ventilation, vehicles can pass on the road. The number of passengers carried by the bus shall not exceed 50% of the approved load. Taxis are not allowed to carry passengers in the front row. column25: From the Announcement No.14 of Hegang City's COVID-19 Work Headquarter, since April 4 2022, the following policies will be implemented.    1. Accommodation can be opened in an orderly manner after passing the inspection and evaluation by the local competent department. All personnel entering the accommodation shall wear masks, enter the door for temperature measurement and code scanning. With a history of living in medium and high-risk areas for nearly 14 days, red and yellow code personnel are not allowed to enter. If such personnel are found, they shall immediately report to the local community for closed-loop control. At the same time, employees should do a good job in daily health monitoring and registration.    2. Closed management shall be implemented for residential areas in the sealed area. All personnel stay at home, and personnel and vehicles cannot enter or leave. Take out and express delivery necessary for basic living shall be delivered without contact and shall not enter the sealed area.    See Guangming Net website. column10: The government of Manzhouli detected 5 cases with positive PCR test result in Manzhouli on 15/Feb/2022. Since schools are still in winter vacation, there is no specific regulations on school closure. But it can be inferred that schools of all levels are closed.    https://web.archive.org/web/20220216050759/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s?src=11&timestamp=1644987946&ver=3623&signature=SsTKNeThJguoCXgudY9V7thtgzUUVliVuCqnwHH1kqvSHU67RTgKps8Ong%2A-6m4QPZHilBLmY--cMYMEIixIetgZIAafwH6RqD5aFDut1UxhdmDNneXrbNgABUJ8NEH4&new=1
column13: The government of Manzhouli required that all businesses with relatively closed spaces, including Mahjong parlors, baths, cinemas, theatres, restaurants, singing halls, dance halls, foot therapy shops, massage shops, game halls, Internet cafes, indoor sports and fitness venues, indoor children's amusement projects, small hotels located in the basement or semi basement, various offline education and training institutions and other places be suspended on 15/Feb/2022.    https://web.archive.org/web/20220216050759/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s?src=11×tamp=1644987946&ver=3623&signature=SsTKNeThJguoCXgudY9V7thtgzUUVliVuCqnwHH1kqvSHU67RTgKps8Ong%2A-6m4QPZHilBLmY--cMYMEIixIetgZIAafwH6RqD5aFDut1UxhdmDNneXrbNgABUJ8NEH4&new=1

column13: On December 30, 2021, the government of  Qinghai Province issued Circular of Qinghai Provincial Headquarters for Prevention, Control and Disposal of Novel Coronavirus Pneumonia (No.4), emphasizing that all key places should strictly implement measures such as staff health management and site environment ventilation and disinfection.    The link: https://archive.vn/xglP7
column16: On December 30, 2021, the government of  Qinghai Province issued Circular of Qinghai Provincial Headquarters for Prevention, Control and Disposal of Novel Coronavirus Pneumonia (No.4), emphasizing that  public places such as tourist attractions and entertainment venues should strictly implement requirements of "limit, reservation and off-peak".    The link:  https://archive.vn/xglP7
column19: On December 30, 2021, the government of  Qinghai Province issued Circular of Qinghai Provincial Headquarters for Prevention, Control and Disposal of Novel Coronavirus Pneumonia (No.4), emphasizing the principle of "not holding training, meetings and all kinds of activities if it is not necessary", and generally not holding large-scale gathering activities, advocating family gatherings with no more than 10 people.    The link: https://archive.vn/xglP7
column22: On December 30, 2021, the government of  Qinghai Province issued Circular of Qinghai Provincial Headquarters for Prevention, Control and Disposal of Novel Coronavirus Pneumonia (No.4), stressing that all types of transport should strictly control the load rate and strengthen regular disinfection.    The link: https://archive.vn/xglP7
column25: On December 30, 2021,  the government of  Qinghai Province issued Circular of Qinghai Provincial Headquarters for Prevention, Control and Disposal of Novel Coronavirus Pneumonia (No.4), urging people to minimize their participation in all kinds of gathering activities and stay in places where people gather.    The link: https://archive.vn/xglP7
column28: On December 30, 2021,  the government of  Qinghai Province issued Circular of Qinghai Provincial Headquarters for Prevention, Control and Disposal of Novel Coronavirus Pneumonia (No.4), emphasizing that all returnees must have nucleic acid test reports within 48 hours, and those who cannot provide nucleic acid test reports should be tested locally and controlled locally before the test results are issued. In addition, "non-essential travel" is advocated, and people in The province are strictly restricted from traveling to medium-high risk areas and areas affected by the epidemic, and non-essential travel to other counties (cities and districts) in the cities where medium-high risk areas are located.    The link: https://archive.vn/xglP7
column42: The Health Commission of Qinghai Province releases the latest news about COVID-19 every day.    The link: https://archive.vn/TCRRU
column53: On December 30, 2021, the government of Qinghai Province issued Circular of Qinghai Provincial Headquarters for Prevention, Control and Disposal of Novel Coronavirus Pneumonia (No.4), urging residents to continue to consolidate good hygiene and disease prevention habits, and minimize their participation in various kinds of gathering activities and stay in places where people gather.    The link: https://archive.vn/xglP7
column59: On December 30, 2021,  the government of Qinghai Province issued Circular of Qinghai Provincial Headquarters for Prevention, Control and Disposal of Novel Coronavirus Pneumonia (No.4), stressing that special places such as nursing homes should strictly implement closed management.    The link: https://archive.vn/xglP7

column10: No policy change was found. The newest policy of Shandong are as follows:  Persons entering or returning from locally affected areas should hold negative nucleic acid test proof within 48 hours and take nucleic acid test again upon arrival at destination.  Persons entering or returning to Shandong from counties (cities, districts and banners) in medium-high risk areas shall be quarantined for 7 days and monitored at home for 7 days upon arrival.  Persons from other counties (cities, districts or banners) in prefecture-level cities with medium-high risk areas entering (returning) Shandong shall hold negative nucleic acid test proof within 48 hours and undergo nucleic acid test once upon arrival.  Persons returning to Or entering Shandong with a history of living in a land border port city within the last 14 days shall take a nucleic acid test upon arrival upon proof of negative nucleic acid test within 48 hours.  URL: http://archive.today/Xg4pb

column28: Outward Travel Policies:  Strict travel restriction to high-risk areas;   Personnel in high-risk positions shall avoid travel as far as possible; People who hold "yellow code" shall fulfill their personal protection responsibilities, actively cooperate with health monitoring and nucleic acid detection, and do not travel until the risk of infection is eliminated;    Inward Travel Policies:  People coming from county (city, district) where the medium and high-risk areas are located are suspended from coming to Shandong.  People from other counties (cities and districts) in the prefecture level city where the medium and high-risk areas are located do not come to Shandong unnecessarily.  People in high-risk Posts outside the province shall try to avoid coming to Shandong.    URL: https://web.archive.org/web/20220216112302/https://m.thepaper.cn/baijiahao_16467767

column22: On January 1, some bus lines in Beilun District of Ningbo were temporarily suspended, some sections of Metro Line 1 were suspended, and all flights from Ningbo to Beijing were cancelled.    http://archive.today/2022.01.12-132904/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/BfMeocGfLQg5iGBONkZk3A
column28: The leading group for epidemic prevention and control in Beilun District of Ningbo decided that from 16:30 on January 1, 2022, Beilun District will start level I emergency response and implement temporary closure management for Beilun District.    http://archive.today/2022.01.12-133249/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/5x-SW_qFX0eAi-TklPyfSg

column10: On December 31, the education and Sports Bureau of Shangyu District, Shaoxing City issued a notice that from Sunday, January 2, 2022, schools and kindergartens in the region will resume offline teaching in an orderly manner.    http://archive.today/2022.01.12-092050/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/NyZz-ujZNnItCwrhoxSb5w
column28: From January 2, Ningbo railway station will resume the implementation of the strict control of cross provincial travel policy according to the provincial epidemic prevention and control requirements: the travel of personnel in Beilun District of Ningbo will be strictly restricted; Personnel from other districts and counties (cities) in Ningbo do not travel unnecessarily. If they really need to travel, they must hold the negative certificate of nucleic acid test within 48 hours. At the same time, in accordance with the requirements of the prevention and control policy of the capital's strict management of joint prevention and control coordination mechanism in Beijing, all ticket sales channels will suspend the sale of tickets from stations in Ningbo (Ningbo, yuyaobei, Yuyao, ZhuangQiao, Fenghua and Ninghai) to stations in Beijing from now on.    http://archive.today/2022.01.12-133510/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/F_grDh0GRklASI-TSCc-_g

column10: Novel coronavirus pneumonia prevention and control work group in Beilun district has decided to start the study. The primary school in the whole district has temporarily stopped teaching from January 4, 2022, and the time for resuming the lessons is announced. In January 2022, the general high school entrance examination and selective examination will be conducted as scheduled from January 6 to 8.    http://archive.today/2022.01.12-134524/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/HTaCTt_GAgD8ALu4Lzz-Xg
column13: On January 4, Ningbo issued a notice that all commercial outlets in Beilun sealed off area were closed, and residents' basic necessities and urgently needed drugs were uniformly organized for door-to-door distribution. In principle, in the control area, each family can assign a family member to go out every two days to purchase living materials.  This indicates that the workplace in the containment area is closed, but it is normal outside the containment area.All cultural, sports, entertainment, religious and other personnel gathering places in the region shall be closed.    http://archive.today/2022.01.12-134735/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/lDCKVXvqZ0nxTKoVj3aoxQ
column19: On January 4, Beilun District of Ningbo issued a notice that all "red affairs" in the whole district would be suspended and "white affairs" would be simplified after the report. All cultural, sports, entertainment, religious and other personnel gathering places in the region shall be closed.    http://archive.today/2022.01.12-134735/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/lDCKVXvqZ0nxTKoVj3aoxQ
column25: Since January 2, the sealed off area of Ningbo has fully implemented closed isolation and staying at home, strictly implemented home isolation control measures, closed all commercial outlets in the area, and uniformly organized door-to-door distribution of residents' basic necessities and urgently needed drugs. In the control area, only personnel can enter and leave, and personnel gathering is strictly prohibited. The prevention area has fully implemented the principle of not leaving unless necessary, and personnel gathering is strictly prohibited. In principle, each family can assign a family member to go out every two days to purchase living materials.  The outside of the sealed area is not subject to this strict policy control requirements.    http://archive.today/2022.01.12-134016/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/D_ereCn3_9CzVEp_Q3wNhQ

column19: On January 5, Yongkang City issued a notice that in the control area, only personnel can not enter and leave, only life support places are open, personnel gathering is strictly prohibited, and in principle, they are isolated at home.    http://archive.today/2022.01.12-141538/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/9Mz5wZAAfjNR7jfnXB37dA
column33: The Fenghua district government of Ningbo issued a notice on January 5 that the on-the-job migrant workers who have celebrated the Spring Festival will be given a one-time subsidy at the standard of 500 yuan / person, which will be cashed in May. A consumption voucher of 500 yuan / person will be given to the on-the-job migrant workers, including 300 yuan for accommodation and catering and 200 yuan for shopping. The service life is from January 30 to February 15.    http://archive.today/2022.01.12-131801/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/rfEVgwYJm4xmpJ3o0n-7Bw

column16: In January 6th, Jinhua issued a circular on the prevention and control of New Coronavirus pneumonia, temporarily shutting down Internet cafes, KTV, bars, chess and card rooms, mahjong, game rooms, table room, room escape, SPA hall, moxibustion hall, bath, foot bath, swimming pool and other indoor closed leisure places. The number of people received in scenic spots, cinemas, libraries, cultural centers, art galleries, museums, gymnasiums and other places in the city shall not exceed 50% of the approved number. Advocate the postponement of "red affairs", "white affairs" and no banquet. Advocate family dinners and gatherings with no more than 10 people.    http://archive.today/2022.01.12-142001/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/ZASNCPZmF0M6LDd0Hd8p3g
column19: In January 6th, Jinhua issued a circular on the prevention and control of New Coronavirus pneumonia, temporarily shutting down Internet cafes, KTV, bars, chess and card rooms, mahjong, game rooms, table room, room escape, SPA hall, moxibustion hall, bath, foot bath, swimming pool and other indoor closed leisure places. The number of people received in scenic spots, cinemas, libraries, cultural centers, art galleries, museums, gymnasiums and other places in the city shall not exceed 50% of the approved number. Advocate the postponement of "red affairs", "white affairs" and no banquet. column10: Since March 7, primary and secondary schools, kindergartens (including private schools), and various training institutions in Jiashan County’s epidemic prevention and control areas, control areas, and prevention areas (Huimin Street) have adopted measures to suspend classes. The specific resumption time depends on the Changes in the epidemic situation will be notified separately.    http://web.archive.org/web/20220309084319/https://new.qq.com/omn/20220307/20220307A037KG00.html  Since March 7, students in primary and secondary schools, kindergartens (including private schools), various training institutions, and closed and controlled areas within the urban area of Kaihua County (Qinyang Office, Chinatown Town) have begun to suspend classes. In principle, teachers and students at the school cannot leave the school. The specific resumption time of classes will be notified separately depending on the change of the epidemic situation.  http://web.archive.org/web/20220309090219/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/m55mjLxIwCLmHHjsnr1pVw
column13: On March 7, Kaihua County completely suspended the operation of online car-hailing within the county.    http://web.archive.org/web/20220309090219/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/m55mjLxIwCLmHHjsnr1pVw
column19: On March 7, the gathering of people in Kaihua County was strictly restricted, and large-scale conferences, sports events, celebrations, exhibitions, annual meetings, lectures, training, recruitment and other gathering activities were suspended. Strictly implement "delaying happy events, simple funerals, and no banquets". Activities such as rural cultural halls and rural family banquets are suspended.    http://web.archive.org/web/20220309152214/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/m55mjLxIwCLmHHjsnr1pVw
column22: On March 7, Kaihua County completely suspended the operation of passenger lines, chartered tours, urban and rural buses, intercity express buses, taxis, and online car-hailing within the county.  http://web.archive.org/web/20220309090219/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/m55mjLxIwCLmHHjsnr1pVw    On March 7, some passenger routes of Cangnan city and urban and rural buses were resumed, but according to the needs of the county prevention and control office's epidemic prevention and control work, in order to ensure the timely transfer of nucleic acid samples and quarantined personnel, the operation of all routes of the village bus was temporarily suspended.  http://web.archive.org/web/20220309094439/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/zLYiVpYNhn27y1II4MlbzQ    From 6:00 on March 7, 2022, the operation of Puyan Station of Hangzhou Metro Line 4 will be suspended.  http://web.archive.org/web/20220309094639/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/bXa71c1o-xCsD-xxAP36ig

column10: On March 8, primary and secondary schools in Cangnan County, Wenzhou resumed offline teaching, and more than 100 primary and secondary schools and kindergartens resumed classes in an orderly manner. But Kaihua is still closed.    http://web.archive.org/web/20220309083908/http://news.66wz.com/system/2022/03/08/105446348.shtml

column13: In March 10th, the leading group of New Coronavirus pneumonia epidemic prevention and control in Lucheng District, Wenzhou: all schools in the region were temporarily suspended. Meetings and other gathering activities will be cancelled; The whole region strictly implements the postponement of weddings, the simplification of funerals and the exclusion of banquets. Restaurants and restaurants in the whole region will cancel Hall Food and encourage customers to pack and take away consumption.  http://archive.today/2022.03.15-152613/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/LfB7ka6Gj3072bjgcJxWUw

column16: On March 11, the press conference of Zhejiang provincial government said: further strengthen social control. Strictly manage personnel gathering places, especially limit the number of people received in indoor closed public places. Strictly implement the management measures of meetings and activities, and advocate "postponement of weddings, simplification of funerals and no banquets" in accordance with the principles of "unnecessary holding" and "online but not offline", so as to reduce the aggregation risk.  http://archive.today/2022.03.15-153338/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/okZENkLTRyxGQm_ -e-redA

column22: Due to the need of epidemic prevention and control, since 6:00 on March 12, 2022, the operation of Qicheng Road station, Qingliu Middle Road station, tangxin line station, Yipeng station, Xinzhen Road station and cangbei Village Station of line 8 of Hangzhou Metro Line 7 has been suspended, and other stations in the whole network have been in normal operation.  http://archive.today/2022.03.15-154309/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/1j5uWzdAZvHmW8B9xSNIsg

column13: On March 13, Hangzhou epidemic prevention and control office issued the notice on strengthening the control of some public places and strictly controlling personnel gathering activities during the epidemic. The notice requires strict management of personnel gathering places. From now on, bars, KTVs, Internet cafes, chess and card rooms, mahjong rooms, board game rooms and other closed places with poor ventilation and crowd gathering will be temporarily closed. The reception scale of some public places shall be controlled and the reasonable spacing shall be maintained. The reception number of public places such as restaurants, teahouses, song and dance entertainment places, entertainment halls, cinemas, gymnasiums, libraries, cultural centers, art galleries, museums, parks and urban tourist attractions shall not exceed 50% of the maximum carrying capacity, The number of participants in religious activities and folk belief activities shall not exceed 50% of the capacity of the place.  Suspend offline teaching of off campus training institutions. From now on, all off campus training institutions in the city will suspend offline teaching and training.  http://archive.today/2022.03.15-154551/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/QLWNUQo98GqSgRKRYJOmXg

column10: On March 14, according to the needs of epidemic prevention and control, Quzhou took the following measures for Education:  1. All primary and secondary schools (including kindergartens) and training institutions at the municipal level and within the two districts will be suspended for one week, and the resumption time will be notified;  2. All students living in boarding schools are subject to the closed management of staying in school, and the general students are suspended from entering the school. Teachers should make scientific regulation and arrangement, and in principle, they can only enter and leave;  3. Colleges and universities and the Yangtze River Delta Research Institute of CETC implement closed management, and faculty and students can only enter and leave;  4. All primary and secondary schools at the municipal level and within the two districts have been adjusted to online teaching, kindergartens have stopped entering the park, and all kinds of training institutions have stopped carrying out offline training.  5. Schools in all localities should do a good job in the dynamic arrangement of the "three areas" involved in the epidemic, and actively cooperate with the implementation of various control measures of relevant personnel. Teachers and students in Kaihua, Qujiang sealed and controlled areas and controlled areas should be under the "14 + 7" control of the community, and teachers and students in the prevention area should be under the "2 + 14" control, which can be picked up by their parents. For students who cannot be picked up if they have difficulties, the school should implement the control measures in a single room.  During the suspension period, we will do a good job in suspension, online teaching services, mental health education for teachers and students and other related work.  http://archive.today/2022.03.15-154933/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/dUGw4LKUF3jc8gyjPEpN0w
column13: On March 14, Quzhou launched level II response. Relevant measures taken temporarily are as follows:  1. Except for supermarkets, shopping malls, pharmacies and other service places necessary for life, all other business places are temporarily closed.  2. Schools, kindergartens and training institutions are temporarily suspended. Except for the enterprises that need epidemic prevention, guarantee people's livelihood and are approved by the headquarters, all other enterprises shall stop work; Compact the main responsibility of the enterprise and implement strict management with the enterprise as the unit. All hospitals implement closed management for existing inpatients. Public transport such as taxis, buses and long-distance passenger vehicles will be suspended.  3. Close the urban expressway intersection, and do not enter or leave in principle  4. Strictly control national and provincial roads. Vehicles can transit and personnel are not allowed to get off.  5. Qujiang District and Kecheng district carry out global nucleic acid detection once a day. Please actively cooperate.  6. Do not go out, get together or gather unless necessary. "Red affairs" will be suspended and "white affairs" will be simplified.  http://archive.today/2022.03.15-155116/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/k -0HyGRgKEmJ0t4ocvh_ qw

column13: On March 15, the epidemic news conference of Zhejiang provincial government said that all kinds of meetings and gathering activities should be strictly controlled, the number of people in crowded places such as stores, supermarkets, hotels, scenic spots and sports venues should be strictly controlled, and measures such as "wearing masks + taking body temperature + scanning code" should be implemented in strict accordance with the regulations.  On March 15, Jiaxing, Zhejiang Province issued the following notice:  1. Temporarily shut down bars, KTVs, Internet cafes, chess and card rooms, mahjong rooms, board game rooms, recreation halls, video game halls, secret room escape, foot bath shops, ear picking shops, health salons, bathrooms, gyms, natatoriums, gymnasiums, cinemas, libraries, museums, cinemas and other closed public places in the city. Suspend the opening of religious and folk belief sites. The number of people in restaurants and restaurants shall be controlled according to 50% of the capacity, and the number of people at a single table shall be controlled below 10.  2. Strictly control the number of various meetings and activities, and strictly control the number of participants in accordance with the principles of "unnecessary holding", "online and offline holding", "who is responsible for holding", "where to hold and where to be responsible". For meetings and activities with more than 50 people, epidemic prevention and control work plans shall be formulated and submitted to the local epidemic prevention and control office for approval.  3. The school implements closed-loop management and suspends offline teaching of off campus training institutions. Special institutions such as nursing homes, child welfare homes and detention centers are under closed management.  http://archive.today/2022.03.15-155627/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/deuMugIhoSi_O2UxFeOqwg  http://archive.today/2022.03.15-160525/http://news.sohu.com/a/529800961_162522

column10: On March 16, Qujiang District and Kecheng District launched level I emergency response.  1. Temporary closure management and traffic control shall be implemented for the whole region, and only entry and exit are allowed.  2. Close all business places, except for vegetable farms, supermarkets, pharmacies and other places necessary for people's life.  3. Schools, kindergartens and training institutions are closed.  4. Except for the enterprises that need epidemic prevention, guarantee people's livelihood and involve major safety, all other enterprises will stop work, and all construction sites will stop work. All hospitals implement closed management for existing inpatients.  5. Public transport such as taxis, buses and long-distance passenger vehicles are suspended; Close the entrances and exits of urban expressway, and do not enter or leave in principle; Strictly control national and provincial roads, vehicles can transit, and personnel are not allowed to get on and off.  6. Do not go out, get together or gather unless necessary. "Red affairs" will be suspended, "white affairs" will be simplified, and banquets will not be held.  http://archive.today/2022.03.16-082313/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/kz5vj5jmN7kMB13IyHC7pw

Except for the enterprises that need epidemic prevention, guarantee people's livelihood and involve major safety, all other enterprises will stop work, and all construction sites will stop work. All hospitals implement closed management for existing inpatients.  5. Public transport such as taxis, buses and long-distance passenger vehicles are suspended; Close the entrances and exits of urban expressway, and do not enter or leave in principle; Strictly control national and provincial roads, vehicles can transit, and personnel are not allowed to get on and off.  6. Do not go out, get together or gather unless necessary. "Red affairs" will be suspended, "white affairs" will be simplified, and banquets will not be held.  http://archive.today/2022.03.16-082313/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/kz5vj5jmN7kMB13IyHC7pw

column10: On April 6, Pingyang County, Wenzhou City issued a notice,  1? The broad masses of citizens in the county do not leave Pingyang or go out of their homes unless necessary;  2? All schools in the county will be temporarily suspended, and all kinds of offline training will be suspended;  3? All public places in confined spaces in the county will be closed temporarily, and other public places, communities and vehicles will strictly implement measures such as temperature measurement, scanning "Wenzhou epidemic prevention code" and "place code", wearing masks and disinfection, and reasonably control the number of personnel;  4? Restaurants and restaurants in the county will cancel Hall Food and encourage customers to pack and take away consumption;  5? The county strictly implements the postponement of weddings, simple funeral and no banquet;  6? In addition to participating in the basic operation of the city, the staff of all organs and institutions in the county fully devote themselves to the front line of epidemic prevention and control on the basis of personal protection;  7? County wide meetings and other gathering activities will be cancelled;  http://archive.today/2022.04.13-134711/https://view.inews.qq.com/a/20220407A037B100    From 0:00 on April 6, Haining City, Jiaxing, Zhejiang Province, upgraded the control measures: close all vegetable farms, supermarkets, pharmacies and all other business places in the city. The living necessities of residents in four streets are distributed. According to the requirements of the village and community, the residents of other towns shall organize the implementation of affordable paid supply, or purchase in an orderly manner at the temporary supply guarantee point. All villages and communities in the city strictly implement the control measures of "personnel are not allowed to leave the house unless necessary, are strictly prohibited from leaving the community, and are strictly prohibited from gathering".  http://archive.today/2022.04.13-133411/https://baijiahao.baidu.com/s?id=1729323865784498540&wfr=spider&for=pc

column10: On April 11, Haining, Zhejiang adjusted the emergency response of major public health emergencies to level II. All schools, kindergartens, childcare institutions and offline training institutions in Haining City have been temporarily suspended. Except for the necessary business places such as supermarkets and service stores, all other business places such as agricultural trade and life markets will be closed temporarily. All kinds of scenic spots are temporarily closed.  Suspend all kinds of literary and artistic performances, exhibitions, sales promotions and other activities. The "red business" is postponed, the "white business" is simplified, and the banquet is not allowed. Restaurants and restaurants are not allowed to eat in the hall, but only for takeout.  Strictly control all kinds of meetings, strictly control the number of participants and postpone the holding of meetings with more than 50 people in accordance with the principles of "no unnecessary holding", "online but not offline", "who is responsible for hosting", "where is responsible for hosting".  Strictly control the high-speed export, and suspend the entry of vehicles in addition to ensuring the transportation of key materials such as production, life and epidemic prevention; Hangzhou Hainan intercity railway, taxis, buses, long-distance passenger vehicles and other public transport were suspended.  http://archive.today/2022.04.13-134350/http://www.zj.chinanews.com.cn/jzkzj/2022 -04-11/detail-ihaxmqeq7515380. shtml  On April 11, a large number of hospitals in Ningbo were closed, and a large number of scenic spots were closed.  http://archive.today/2022.04.13-133230/https://www.163.com/dy/article/H4MRSJJ705259VI8.html

column13: Since 0:00 on April 12, the level II emergency response of public health emergencies in Tongxiang City has been adjusted to level III emergency response.  Continue to close chess and card rooms, bars, discos, KTVs, mahjong rooms, teahouses, tea rooms, board games rooms, swimming pools, public bathrooms, foot therapy (bath) shops, Internet cafes, cinemas, cinemas, recreation halls, video game halls, script killing, secret room escape, massage shops, moxibustion shops, beauty salons, spas, pedicure shops, infant bathing places, children's entertainment projects, stadiums, billiards rooms, gyms, ear picking shops Health salons and other indoor closed places for entertainment and leisure and religious (folk belief) places. Other business premises and production enterprises should strictly implement epidemic prevention and control measures and resume work and production in an orderly manner.  Suspend the organization of large-scale square dance, aerobics and other gathering recreational activities.  Visits to nursing homes, welfare homes, psychiatric hospitals and other key places will be suspended.  Schools, kindergartens and kindergartens resume school in an orderly manner and implement closed-loop management; All kinds of offline early education and training institutions continued to suspend the opening of school.  The number of tourists received by scenic spots shall not exceed 50% of the maximum carrying capacity, and the number of people received by libraries and museums shall not exceed 50% of the approved number.  "Red affairs are postponed, white affairs are simplified and banquets are not held", and rural cultural auditorium and rural family banquet activities are suspended; Restaurants, restaurants and other restaurants shall control the number of people according to 50% of the capacity, and encourage customers to pack and take away for consumption.  http://archive.today/2022.04.13-134528/https://www.163.com/dy/article/H4M95FOS0552E52Z.html

column10: Primary and secondary schools, vocational schools, colleges and universities, and private kindergartens within the Binhai New Area of Tianjin will suspend all educational and teaching activities. https://archive.vn/DKWuh

column16: On January 12, Tianjin demanded the closure of general public places, the suspension of the opening of various religious places, and the suspension of collective religious activities. https://archive.vn/nyKzv
column19: On January 12, Tianjin issued the "Proposal for Epidemic Prevention and Control in Rural Areas of the City", which clearly stated that the holding of wedding ceremonies, brief funerals, and banquets would be suspended, and gathering activities such as village meetings and literary and art gatherings would be suspended. https://archive.vn/yoN5k

column22: Zhejiang Yongkang will resume the whole bus line from January 22.     http://archive.today/2022.01.26-062703/https://new.qq.com/omn/20220121/20220121A07SNC00.html

column19: On January 23, 2022, Beijing designated Fengtai District as a prevention zone, and fengtai district was required to strengthen various epidemic prevention and control measures and suspend gathering activities.    See website: https://archive.vn/Q3pUA    See website: https://archive.vn/Q3pUA
column22: On 23 January, 2022, the full load ratio of rail transit and ground bus is adjusted to 75% in Beijing Fengtai District.     See website: https://archive.vn/Q3pUA
column59: On 23 January, 2022, the elderly care institutions in Beijing Fengtai District are closed.     See website: https://archive.vn/Q3pUA

column13: In Xi'an, shopping malls, supermarkets, and stores along the street have resumed business since Jan.24th.     https://archive.vn/p0JIF#selection-271.0-271.33
column16: In Xi'an, public events can be hold but it is need to limit the number of participants to 50.     https://archive.vn/p0JIF#selection-309.15-309.30
column19: It is recommended that no more than 10 people participate family dinner parties. It is recommended to delay wedding ceremony and simplify funerals and no banquets in XI'an.     https://archive.vn/p0JIF#selection-319.2-323.76
column22: In Xi'an, buses, taxis, online car-hailing, subways, bus lines and other means of transportation have resumed operations in an all-round way, and drivers and passengers need to take personal protection since Jan.24th.   On 23 January, 2022, the full load ratio of rail transit and ground bus is adjusted to 75% in Beijing Fengtai District.     https://archive.vn/p0JIF  https://archive.vn/Q3pUA
column25: From January 24, 2022, Xi'an City will be reduced to a low-risk area.   https://archive.vn/p0JIF#selection-171.0-183.12
column28: As for Xi'an, people in low-risk areas outside the city can return with a 48-hour negative nucleic acid test certificate, a communication big data itinerary card, and Xi'an "One Code Pass" with a green code.     https://archive.vn/p0JIF#selection-213.13-221.37

column10: Zhejiang Jinhua Yongkang Education Bureau decided to resume classes in primary and secondary schools in the city in an orderly manner from January 21.    https://archive.vn/USOyq
